Parents heartbroken over daughters' tragic death in US plane crash
2013-07-08 03:58:13 GMT
A Boeing 777 jetliner with 307 people on board crashed in landing at San Francisco International Airport on  Saturday. Two teenage girls from Jiangshan Senior High School, Zhejiang Province were confirmed killed in the  accident. The two girls were supposed to enjoy their summer camp and embrace their short stay in America. The accident no doubt has broken their dreams and hearts of the whole family.
